I am honored to have spent the last three years of my career here. The people inside the building are what make it special. Although we didn’t get to hoist the Lombardi, we sure did have a great time chasing it.

Thank you for embracing me.

To commemorate his 100-sack career milestone, @calaiscampbell and his @crcfoundation are supporting 100 teachers in the four cities he has played in with a $100,000 donation benefitting under-resourced schools through @kidsinneed.

The initiative will provide each teacher with $500 of essential school supplies and $500 to purchase other classroom resources. Additionally, Calais will donate $10,000 to Denver South and South Miami teachers to pay homage to where he played high school and college football.

Please join us in congratulating Executive Committee member AND newest member of the 1️⃣0️⃣0️⃣ sack club, @calaiscampbell 👏. He's celebrating his latest achievement by giving back to teachers all across the U.S. with a $100,000 donation through @kidsinneed.

I love this game with all my heart. And the best part of this game is sacking the QB! 30 years ago when I first I stepped on the football field I was put at DE to apply pressure and set the edge. I fell in love with it immediately. And when I learned about the 100 Sack Club, my number one goal became to one day be a part of it. And it is so amazing when your dreams come true. All the hard work and dedication paid off. I’m happy to finally be here and I sincerely enjoyed the journey!

Shoutout to all the fans that rooted for me and supported me over the years!

We ain’t done yet!
Calais Campbell is the newest member of the 100-Sack Club, joining a legendary group of defenders. Since 1960, he is the 63rd player with 100 recorded sacks.

Our Week 7 #CommunityMVP turned a career milestone into a celebration for others. 🎉

@CalaisCampbell donated $100K in honor of his 100th sack to teachers in under-resourced schools. He recently added another $50K to impact more teachers across the U.S.

Even more—Calais and his wife Rocio visited young patients at Children’s Healthcare of Atlanta this past summer. They also surprised 10 single moms and their kids with $500 grocery gift cards to help lighten their financial load.

Read about all of our #CommunityMVP winners at the link in our bio.
